code_changes.content:
{
  "buggy_files": [
    "drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c"
  ],
  "buggy_functions": [
    "iwl_dev_info_table"
  ],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The bug report indicates missing PCI subdevice entries for device 0x2526 (iwl9260) with subdevice IDs 0x4010, 0x4018, and 0x401C. The iwl_dev_info_table in drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c (lines 978-997) is responsible for mapping PCI device and subdevice IDs to device configurations for firmware loading. Currently, the table contains entries for 0x2526 with subdevices 0x0010, 0x0014, 0x0018, 0x001C, 0x6010, 0x6014, 0x8014, 0x8010, 0xA014, 0xE010, and 0xE014, but it is missing entries for 0x4010, 0x4018, and 0x401C. These missing entries prevent the driver from properly identifying and configuring the Intel 9260 cards with those specific subdevice IDs, causing firmware loading to fail. The fix requires adding three new IWL_DEV_INFO entries mapping device 0x2526 with subdevices 0x4010, 0x4018, and 0x401C to the iwl9260_2ac_160_cfg configuration."
}

